Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.07,Caption,,0,0,0,,Ariane 5 went on to become one of the\Nmost
Dialogue: 10,0:00:04.07,0:00:07.73,Caption,,0,0,0,,successful rockets in history — it flew\Nfor another
Dialogue: 10,0:00:07.73,0:00:11.39,Caption,,0,0,0,,twenty-seven years. They found the bug.\NThey fixed the
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.39,0:00:13.43,Caption,,0,0,0,,redundancy. They asked the questions.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:13.77,0:00:17.84,Caption,,0,0,0,,But the first one paid for that lesson\Nin thirty-seven
Dialogue: 10,0:00:17.84,0:00:21.10,Caption,,0,0,0,,seconds and three hundred and seventy\Nmillion dollars.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:21.44,0:00:24.84,Caption,,0,0,0,,Every disaster starts as a decision that\Nmade sense at
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.84,0:00:28.24,Caption,,0,0,0,,the time. That's the whole job of this\Nchannel —
Dialogue: 10,0:00:28.24,0:00:31.64,Caption,,0,0,0,,to go back and find the exact moment the\Nsense
Dialogue: 10,0:00:31.64,0:00:32.32,Caption,,0,0,0,,ran out.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.66,0:00:35.85,Caption,,0,0,0,,I'm going to keep putting failures on\Nthis table. If
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.85,0:00:39.04,Caption,,0,0,0,,you want to be here when I do —\Nsubscribe,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:39.04,0:00:41.60,Caption,,0,0,0,,and I'll see you at the next one.
